title: Percentage of childless women , by age U.S. 2018
summary: The chart at hand is a line chart where the x axis denotes Year and a y axis denotes Percentage of childless women. In total the number of data points it has is 7.
Overall Percentage of childless women has decreased over the Year.
Percentage of childless women is slightly decreasing from 15_to_19_years_old to 35_to_39_years_old, and finally roughly constant from 35_to_39_years_old to 45_to_50_years_old.
The steepest decrease occurs in between the Year 20_to_24_years_old and 25_to_29_years_old.
Maximum Percentage of childless women, about 96.9 was reported at Year 15_to_19_years_old
Minimum Percentage of childless women about 15.0 was reached at Year 40_to_44_years_old
